type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Vernon in Eure, France, named from the Gaulish element <i>ver(n)</i> ‘alder’ + the Gallo-Roman locative suffix <i>-o</i> (genitive <i>-ōnis</i>).","French: habitational name from the same place as in 1 above or from any of several other places in France with the same name and etymology."],"variants":[{"name":"Varnon","meanings":["English (Leicestershire and Northamptonshire): variant of   Vernon  ."]}]},{"name":"Matheus","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Alfredo, Manuel, Gustavo, Rafael, Alejandro, Arnoldo, Eduardo, Elva, Ernesto, Genoveva, Gerardo, Germano.","German and Flemish: from the personal name <i>Matheus</i> (see   Matthew  ). Compare   Mattice  .","Portuguese: variant of   Mateus  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Matthew","meanings":["form of the name of the Christian evangelist, author of the first gospel in the New Testament. His name is a form of the Hebrew name <i>Mattathia</i>, meaning ‘gift of God’, which is fairly common in the Old Testament, being rendered in the Authorized Version in a number of different forms: <i>Mattan(i)ah</i>, <i>Mattatha(h)</i>, <i>Mattithiah</i>, <i>Mattathias</i>, and so on. In the Authorized Version, the evangelist is regularly referred to as <i>Matthew</i>, while the apostle chosen to replace Judas Iscariot is distinguished as   Matthias .  A related name from the same Hebrew roots, but reversed, is   Jonathan .  Throughout the English-speaking world <i>Matthew</i> has been particularly popular since the 1970s."]},{"name":"Mattice","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Matheus   or perhaps of some similar (like-sounding) cognate, e.g.   Mathes  ,   Mathis   or   Mattis  .","History: The first American bearer of the surname <i>Mattice</i> was Hendrick Mattice, born in Germany, who arrived in NY in 1710. His father's surname was reportedly <i>Matheus</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Matheus Vernon was born in 1151, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Mattheus Vernon. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1151–":"1151–Surnud","1148–Male":"1148–Surnud","1175–1268":"1175–1268","1178–1248":"1178–1248","1151–Female":"1151–Surnud","1248":"1248","1148":"1148","1268":"1268","1178":"1178","1175":"1175","1151":"1151","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hulgreave, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lancaster, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1151–":"1151–Kuollut","1148–Male":"1148–Kuollut","1175–1268":"1175–1268","1178–1248":"1178–1248","1151–Female":"1151–Kuollut","1248":"1248","1148":"1148","1268":"1268","1178":"1178","1175":"1175","1151":"1151","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hulgreave, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lancaster, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1151–":"1151–Décédée","1148–Male":"1148–Décédé","1175–1268":"1175–1268","1178–1248":"1178–1248","1151–Female":"1151–Décédée","1248":"1248","1148":"1148","1268":"1268","1178":"1178","1175":"1175","1151":"1151","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hulgreave, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Lancaster, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancaster, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Matheus Vernon est née en 1151, à Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Mattheus Vernon. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1151–":"1151–Verstorben","1148–Male":"1148–Verstorben","1175–1268":"1175–1268","1178–1248":"1178–1248","1151–Female":"1151–Verstorben","1248":"1248"